Alpaca doesn't support futures - they do stocks and crypto. For futures paper trading, I'd recommend Interactive Brokers - they have the most comprehensive API (ibapi), support all major futures contracts, and their paper trading is rock solid. Alternative: Polygon.io for data + a custom paper trading engine if you want maximum control.

For indicators, I'd stack these (in order of reliability for your 80% target):

RSI (14) - overbought/oversold signals
MACD - momentum + trend confirmation
Bollinger Bands - volatility breakouts
EMA crossovers (9/21/50) - trend direction
Volume confirmation - validate breakouts aren't fake
Plus pull in market sentiment data from APIs like Finnhub or Alpha Vantage to cross-reference before entering positions.

Architecture for cloud + Android-first:

Backend: Node.js + Express on AWS Lambda (serverless, scales automatically, paper trading runs 24/7)
Database: PostgreSQL for trade history/positions
Trading logic: Run the indicator calculations every 5m via CloudWatch events
Android app: React Native (one codebase, Android first, Windows later via Electron)
Real-time: WebSocket connection so the app sees signals/fills instantly
